y, and a host of other methodological and discursive modes. This collection provides not only a fitting tribute to one of the most fascinating figures of Russian letters but also a remarkable picture of the shape of Russian literary scholarship today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aMotion pictureszSoviet UnionxHistory and criticism. 0aRussian literaturexHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh  aAvant-Garde.  aModernism.  aPoetics.  aRussian culture.  aRussian literature.  aStructuralism.1 aAnemone, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBethea, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBezrodny, Mikhail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBodrova, Alina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBogomolov, Nikolai, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBowlt, John E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBozovic, Marijeta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBulgakowa, Oksana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDobritsyn, Andrei, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDolinin, Alexander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEpstein, Mikhail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldberg, Stuart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGolstein, Vladimir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGronas, Mikhail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHansen-Löve, Aage, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb